[The Asian longhorned tick continues to be found in new states. Now, Rhode Island can be added to the 13 states where the tick has been found so far. The USA Department of Agriculture has a table listing the 1st date of Asian longhorned tick detections by state, county, and host as of 14 Sep 2020 for all states, except Ohio.
https://www.aphis.usda.gov/animal_health/animal_diseases/tick/downloads/longhorned-tick-sitrep.pdf
Arkansas
Connecticut
Delaware
Kentucky
Maryland
New Jersey
New York
